<br>
Damn was I wrong.  15int 20hp 25mana 25svmagic(!!) and 25svpoison(!)  Holy hell... where did my staff of the wheel go.. I know I saw it around here somewhere.. =)<br>
<br>
Ok so now I have this skull staff with hands-down AWESOME resistances.  I looked at the other two staves and they also have AWESOME resistances for other encounters...<br>
<br>
Then I look at the Staff of the Four..<br>
<br>
Um.  Why do the resistances on the SotF not live up to the resistances on these staves?  Granted 25 to all might be a bit much, but come on.. 5 and 10?<br>
<br>
I don't want to sound like I'm whining or anything, I'm just curious as to the reasoning behind it.. anyone know? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/01 12:09:51 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok.. resist question.</span><hr size=1> Every epic in the game has another item in the game that is technically better in many respects.  That is one of the difficulties of developing epic quests and THEN adding expansions onto the game that keep up with the rising number of level 60's.  That is one of the reasons that the Epic Armor quests are being developed.<br>
<br>
Keep this in mind, the SotF is the best all around wizard staff in the game.  There are other staves with one or two stats better, but no effect.  And other staves with no real stats but maybe a better effect, depending on whether you like a nuke vs extra protection.  Believe it or not, it is the effect that makes ALL the difference.  We can stay solo on multi group raids.  Which saves clerics TONS in healing mana.  Throw in some extra resists, a large amount of mana, a huge amount of INT(which means you can now dump other INT items for even HIGHER resists) and you begin to see why it is a nice addition.<br>
<br>
Your question is a valid one.  And add this to the mix.  You could technically come up with higher resist combinations by mixing and matching armor rather than questing an entire set of Icicle.  It's the same principal.<br>
<br>
I personally plan on going back for a couple of those staves for my different changes of clothes for different raids to truly max out resists.  But for overall encounters, I'd rather have that effect up and running all the time.  It is really a personal preference issue.  If you finish the quest, you won't regret it.  Just have to give up a little to get a lot. <p><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith3.gif" border="0"><BR>60th Generation Sorcerer of Cazic - Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/01 11:57:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok.. resist question.</span><hr size=1> Our epic has one of the best sets of stats out of all of the epics, trust me, you can put those resistances up somewhere else.  I do think we should have had +20 sv Cold / Fire / Magic and no disease, poison personally. <p><BR>
